@startuml intra_storage_device_vertical_data_tiering
title Intra-Storage Device Vertical Data Tiering Architecture\nLUNs migrate between graded disk tiers inside a single storage device

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam roundcorner 6
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #EAF2F8
  BorderColor #2874A6
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FDEBD0
  DiamondBorderColor #B9770E
}
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #EAF2F8
  BorderColor #2874A6
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #D5F5E3
  BorderColor #1E8449
}

' Structural overview
package "Cloud Storage Device" as csd {
  database "Disk Group 1\n(lower-grade tier)" as dg1
  database "Disk Group 2\n(higher-grade tier)" as dg2
  database "Disk Group n\n(higher tiers)" as dgn

  component "Storage Controller" as sc
  component "LUN Migration Program" as lm
  component "Storage Management\nProgram" as smp
}

component "Automated Scaling\nListener" as asl
component "Pay-Per-Use Monitor" as ppm

actor "Cloud Service\nConsumers" as csc

csc -down-> sc : storage requests
sc -down-> dg1
sc -down-> dg2
sc -down-> dgn

asl -right-> smp : threshold reached
smp -right-> lm : request migration
lm -down-> sc : move LUN between\ngraded tiers
ppm -up-> dg1 : track tier-based\nusage cost
ppm -up-> dg2
ppm -up-> dgn

note right of csd
  Disks (e.g., SATA, SAS, SSD)
  are organized into graded tiers
  by I/O performance.
  LUNs can move up or down to
  match processing and storage
  requirements.
end note

note left of asl
  Tiering workflow:
  1. Group disks into tiers (1)(2)
  2. Place LUNs on a tier (3)
  3. Listener watches thresholds (4)
  4. Pay-per-use tracks usage (5)
  5. Listener informs SMP (6)
  6. SMP signals LUN migration (7)
  7. Migration moves LUN with
     storage controller (8)
  8. New tier yields new
     usage price (9)
end note

@enduml
